```yaml
language: rust
rule:
  pattern: |
    q.par_iter_mut().for_each(|(mult, mut vel)| {
      vel.dx *= mult.0;
      vel.dy *= mult.0;
    });
```
**Why:** Reviewer required that all three velocity components (dx, dy, dz) be scaled by SpeedMultiplier to preserve verticality as a first-class concern (Tenet 2 — Verticality as First-Class). Scaling only dx/dy silently drops vertical velocity.
